Wash and dry all produce. Adjust rack to middle position and preheat oven to
425 degrees. Halve, peel, and thinly slice @Yellow Onion{1}. Pick and finely
chop enough @Rosemary{1/4%ounce} leaves to give you 1 TBSP. Halve
@Yukon Gold Potatoes{16%ounce} lengthwise, then cut into 1-inch-thick wedges
(like steak fries).

Toss potatoes on a #baking sheet{} with chopped rosemary and a large drizzle of
@olive oil{2%teaspoon}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Roast in oven until
lightly browned and crisp, ~{30-35%minutes}.

== Tangy Cabbage ==

Heat a large drizzle of @vegetable oil{1%tablespoon} in a #medium pan{} over
medium-high heat. Add onion and @shredded red cabbage{4%ounce}. Cook, tossing,
until softened, about ~{5%minutes}. Stir in @mustard seeds{1%teaspoon} and cook
until they start to pop, about ~{1%minute}. Stir in @white wine vinegar{5%teaspoon},
@sugar{1%teaspoon}, and a pinch of @salt{}. Reduce heat to low, cover, and cook
until tender, about ~{10%minutes}.

== Steak and Sauce ==

While cabbage cooks, heat a drizzle of oil in another medium pan over
medium-high heat. Pat @sirloin steak{12%ounce} dry with a #paper towel{}, then
season all over with salt and pepper. Add to pan and cook until it reaches
desired doneness, ~{4-7%minutes} per side. Remove from pan and set aside to
rest.

Add @balsamic vinegar{1/2%tablespoon}, @soy sauce{1.5%tablespoon},
@cranberry jam{4%teaspoon}, and @water{3%tablespoon} to pan used for steak over
medium heat (we sent more vinegar and soy sauce). Stir to combine. Let simmer
until reduced to a syrupy consistency, ~{2-3%minutes}. Remove from heat.

Thinly slice steak against the grain. Divide steak, potatoes, and cabbage
between plates. Drizzle sauce over steak and serve.